{"body": "The problem is that the behavior is not consistent, regardless of how you intend to use the `bird` object. Allowing this style of validation means that an object can remain in the database even if it is actually invalid.\r\n\r\nIf this is actually the behavior you want, I would make it so that a bird cannot be deleted if it leaves a pirate bird-less. That way the behavior is consistent regardless of how you access the objects.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4485881", "created_at": "2012-03-13T20:50:14Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5413#issuecomment-4485881", "updated_at": "2012-03-13T20:50:14Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5413, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/panthomakos", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/22a9bb6a9ec077e4d666d98052790c05?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd11f0caf58f8bf7c3bdedb631acfaa64.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/received_events", "gravatar_id": "22a9bb6a9ec077e4d666d98052790c05", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "panthomakos", "type": "User", "id": 186424, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/panthomakos/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381885bd3543c15100e066"}, "id": 4485881, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5413"}
